#: features.js:930
msgid "The Pomodoro technique 🍅"
msgstr "Pomodoro-teknikken 🍅"

#: features.js:932
msgid ""
"In the late 1980s, university student Francesco Cirillo couldn't focus on "
"his studies. He bet himself he could stay concentrated for just a few "
"minutes and reached for the first timer he could find — a kitchen one shaped "
"like a tomato. In Italian, a tomato is a “pomodoro”, and that's how the "
"method got its name."
msgstr ""
"I slutningen af 1980'erne kunne den studerende Francesco Cirillo ikke "
"koncentrere sig om sine studier. Han væddede med sig selv om, at han kunne "
"holde fokus i bare et par minutter, og greb den første den bedste timer, han "
"kunne finde — en køkkentimer formet som en tomat. På italiensk hedder en "
"tomat “pomodoro” — og sådan fik metoden sit navn."

#: features.js:933
msgid ""
"The idea is simple: big tasks feel daunting, but a single pomodoro doesn't. "
"Promise yourself just 25 minutes of focus on one task, and starting becomes "
"easy."
msgstr ""
"Idéen er enkel: store opgaver virker skræmmende, men en enkelt pomodoro gør "
"ikke. Lov dig selv bare 25 minutters fokus på én opgave, så bliver det let "
"at komme i gang."

#: features.js:934
msgid ""
"The classic rhythm:\n"
"• About 25 minutes — one task, nothing else.\n"
"• A 5-minute breather — step away from the screen.\n"
"• After four pomodoros, take a longer 15–30 minute break."
msgstr ""
"Den klassiske rytme:\n"
"• Omkring 25 minutter — én opgave, intet andet.\n"
"• En pause på 5 minutter — gå væk fra skærmen.\n"
"• Efter fire pomodoroer holder du en længere pause på 15–30 minutter."

#: features.js:935
msgid ""
"This is a starting point, not a rule — the applet lets you change any "
"interval and save your own presets."
msgstr ""
"Det er et udgangspunkt, ikke en regel — appletten lader dig ændre ethvert "
"interval og gemme dine egne forudindstillinger."

#: features.js:936
msgid ""
"And it's not just a productivity fad: the exact numbers are flexible, but "
"the principles behind them are backed by attention research. Staying on one "
"task without switching saves energy — getting back on track after an "
"interruption takes about 23 minutes on average. And regular pauses help you "
"hold focus for longer without burning out."
msgstr ""
"Og det er ikke bare en produktivitetstrend: de præcise tal er fleksible, men "
"principperne bag dem understøttes af forskning i opmærksomhed. At blive på "
"én opgave uden at skifte sparer energi — efter en afbrydelse tager det i "
"gennemsnit omkring 23 minutter at komme tilbage. Og regelmæssige pauser "
"hjælper dig med at holde fokus længere uden at brænde ud."

#: features.js:937
msgid ""
"Tip: when something distracts you, don't drop what you're doing — jot the "
"thought down and come back to it on your break. Every finished pomodoro is a "
"small win that keeps your momentum going."
msgstr ""
"Tip: når noget distraherer dig, så slip ikke det, du er i gang med — skriv "
"tanken ned, og vend tilbage til den i pausen. Hver fuldført pomodoro er en "
"lille sejr, der holder dit momentum i gang."

